WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:03.969
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.037 --> 00:05.705
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.772 --> 00:07.240
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.307 --> 00:08.641
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.708 --> 00:10.543
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.610 --> 00:13.980
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.047 --> 00:15.048
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.483
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.549 --> 00:17.650
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.717 --> 00:19.386
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.421
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:22.922
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.924
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.991 --> 00:28.061
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.128 --> 00:29.396
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.462 --> 00:30.597
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.637
<i>[surf rock]</i>

00:37.704 --> 00:43.643
<i>♪</i> ♪

00:43.710 --> 00:46.646
<i>[ominous music]</i>

00:46.713 --> 00:47.814
<i>♪</i> ♪

00:47.881 --> 00:50.417
[maniacal laughter]

00:50.483 --> 00:53.186
{\an1}- Game over, Ace Savvy
and One-Eyed Jack!

00:53.253 --> 00:55.221
- Think again, Wild Card Willy!

00:55.288 --> 00:58.858
{\an1}I've got a few more cards
up my sleeve.

00:58.925 --> 01:01.561
[horn honking]

01:01.628 --> 01:05.432
- All right girls,
let's deal with these losers.

01:07.066 --> 01:09.736
<i>♪</i> ♪

01:09.803 --> 01:11.638
- Eep! Get them!

01:13.840 --> 01:16.376
{\an3}- You take the baby.
I'll take the princess.

01:16.443 --> 01:19.579
{\an3}- Excuse you.
I am the queen.

01:22.382 --> 01:24.350
- Aah!
- [grunts]

01:27.654 --> 01:29.255
- Aah!

01:31.724 --> 01:34.527
- Get ready to do
the bad-guy shuffle.

01:35.995 --> 01:38.598
[electric guitar]

01:38.665 --> 01:40.600
- No aces in this hole.

01:43.736 --> 01:45.205
[footsteps running]

01:46.739 --> 01:48.441
- 52 pick-up!

01:49.876 --> 01:52.846
- Or more precisely, six.

01:52.912 --> 01:54.714
Make that seven.

01:55.982 --> 01:58.284
- Hey guys,
check out my new outfit.

01:58.351 --> 02:00.019
It's perfect for fall weather

02:00.086 --> 02:02.255
and springing into action!

02:04.457 --> 02:07.694
Ugh, these belts are so '90s.

02:13.433 --> 02:15.201
- Wild Card's getting away!

02:15.268 --> 02:17.403
- Hey, Willy, go fish!

02:21.875 --> 02:23.176
- Aah!

02:24.410 --> 02:26.012
Wah!

02:26.079 --> 02:30.450
- I see your bet and raise you!
[laughs]

02:34.954 --> 02:38.224
- Willy, why do you always
have to play dirty cards?

02:38.291 --> 02:40.360
- 'Cause that's the only way
to clean up.

02:40.426 --> 02:44.163
{\an8}So, I guess it's off to jail
for me.

02:44.230 --> 02:45.698
{\an8}[together] The end.

02:45.765 --> 02:46.966
{\an1}- That was sick!
- Awesome!

02:47.033 --> 02:48.668
{\an1}- Where'd you get the idea
for all those

02:48.735 --> 02:50.236
butt-kicking super ladies?

02:50.303 --> 02:53.540
{\an3}- From my sisters.
They've always got my back.

02:53.606 --> 02:54.541
Except for Lola.

02:54.607 --> 02:56.543
{\an3}You never turn your back
on Lola.

02:56.609 --> 02:58.411
{\an1}- So if you fellas win
the contest,

02:58.478 --> 03:01.581
they'll make this here
into a real Ace Savvy comic?

03:01.648 --> 03:04.684
- And we'll get to meet
the creator, Bill Buck!

03:04.751 --> 03:06.152
<i>- Bill Buck!</i>

03:06.219 --> 03:08.454
- Well, I think your comic's
totally gonna win.

03:08.521 --> 03:10.356
{\an1}- Darn tootin'.
- Word.

03:10.423 --> 03:13.726
{\an3}- Loud, McBride, school time is
meant for learning,

03:13.793 --> 03:16.162
{\an3}not for doodling
degenerate fantasies.

03:16.229 --> 03:19.265
This trash belongs to me now.

03:19.332 --> 03:21.634
- But Principal Huggins,
you can't take our comic!

03:21.701 --> 03:24.203
- Oh, and now you're
giving me sass?

03:24.270 --> 03:27.407
That's detention!
Today. Till 5:00.

03:27.473 --> 03:29.242
{\an1}- But we have to get
to the post office by 4:00.

03:29.309 --> 03:30.944
That's the contest deadline.

03:31.010 --> 03:34.614
{\an3}- Oh, I didn't realize.
I'll just give it back to you.

03:34.681 --> 03:36.983
{\an3}Not!

03:37.050 --> 03:38.418
<i>I've got just the thing</i>

03:38.484 --> 03:40.820
to keep those doodling hands
of yours busy:

03:40.887 --> 03:42.822
cleaning erasers.

03:44.724 --> 03:47.527
{\an3}- But we're not criminals.
All we did was make a comic.

03:47.594 --> 03:49.529
And we're getting it back.

03:49.596 --> 03:50.763
{\an3}[grunting]

03:50.830 --> 03:53.466
{\an3}Dang it. He locked us in
from the outside.

03:56.135 --> 03:57.537
{\an1}- [snarls]

03:58.938 --> 04:02.008
{\an1}- Okay, plan B:
we'll sharpen a bunch of pencils

04:02.075 --> 04:04.077
and dig our way out.

04:04.143 --> 04:06.479
- Or I could just pick the lock.

04:06.546 --> 04:08.648
Not that your idea wasn't great.

04:08.715 --> 04:11.084
{\an1}- Lola?
Why are you busting us out?

04:11.150 --> 04:14.354
{\an3}- 'Cause we heard about Huggins
confiscating your comic book.

04:14.420 --> 04:17.322
- The one starring me
as Queen of Diamonds.

04:17.390 --> 04:19.158
- And me as The Royal Flush.

04:19.225 --> 04:21.494
{\an3}- You think we're gonna let
some power-tripping principal

04:21.560 --> 04:23.663
{\an3}take away our chance
to get famous?

04:23.730 --> 04:25.498
{\an3}- Sweet! Now we just got
to find a way

04:25.565 --> 04:28.201
{\an3}to sneak into Huggins' office
and get our comic back.

04:28.267 --> 04:29.769
- Maybe we can use your pencils.

04:29.836 --> 04:32.005
- Forget that. Hop on.

04:32.071 --> 04:33.539
- I tried, buddy.

04:37.477 --> 04:39.979
We got to find a way to get
Huggins out of his office.

04:40.046 --> 04:41.581
- It's taken care of.

04:41.648 --> 04:44.017
- Principal Huggins!
Principal Huggins!

04:44.083 --> 04:46.285
We have got a situation
in the gym!

04:46.352 --> 04:49.956
- Aah!
[bats squeaking]

04:50.023 --> 04:51.824
- I'm on it!

04:53.192 --> 04:55.028
- Now we have
to distract Cheryl.

04:55.094 --> 04:56.362
- It's taken care of.

04:56.429 --> 04:58.331
- Hello, Cheryl.
I took the liberty

04:58.398 --> 04:59.799
of assessing the school budget,

04:59.866 --> 05:03.369
{\an1}and encountered numerous
instances of wasteful spending.

05:03.436 --> 05:05.304
- Oh, that's very cute, sweetie,

05:05.371 --> 05:08.608
but I'm sure everything here is
in order.

05:08.675 --> 05:11.210
{\an1}- Item one:
the two dozen fresh cut roses

05:11.277 --> 05:13.446
you sent to yourself
on Secretary's Day.

05:13.513 --> 05:15.048
Put on a pot of coffee,
sweetie.

05:15.114 --> 05:16.716
We're gonna be here a while.

05:21.521 --> 05:24.590
- Come on. Come on.
Where is it?

05:24.657 --> 05:25.858
{\an3}- There!

05:25.925 --> 05:27.493
- Problem solved, Cheryl.

05:27.560 --> 05:30.329
We got rid of the bats,
and Coach is resting comfortably

05:30.396 --> 05:32.565
after his rabies shot.

05:34.367 --> 05:36.502
I'm headed home for the day.

05:36.569 --> 05:39.539
You can let Loud and McBride out
of detention at 5:00,

05:39.605 --> 05:42.742
but only if the erasers are
clean.

05:45.278 --> 05:46.446
- [gasps] Oh, no!

05:46.512 --> 05:48.247
{\an1}Huggins just took our comic
home with him!

05:48.314 --> 05:52.151
{\an3}- And worse: we didn't finish
cleaning the erasers!

05:52.218 --> 05:53.986
- There goes Huggins!

05:54.053 --> 05:55.288
{\an1}How are we gonna catch up
to him?

05:55.354 --> 05:58.091
- It's taken care of.

05:58.157 --> 05:59.926
- Lincoln, where have you been?

05:59.992 --> 06:02.361
{\an3}The post office closes
in 30 minutes!

06:02.428 --> 06:05.131
- Change of plans.
Principal Huggins has the comic.

06:05.198 --> 06:07.200
Follow that golf cart,
High Card.

06:07.266 --> 06:08.901
- Let's rock, dudes!

06:08.968 --> 06:11.904
[rock music]

06:11.971 --> 06:13.673
<i>♪</i> ♪

06:13.740 --> 06:14.707
- [humming]

06:14.774 --> 06:15.742
♪ Ooh girl ♪

06:15.808 --> 06:17.610
♪ If I could
ooh girl ♪

06:17.677 --> 06:19.612
- I got eyes on the comic.

06:21.981 --> 06:23.916
- Yeesh!

06:23.983 --> 06:25.184
- Raccoon!

06:25.251 --> 06:27.386
[all shouting]

06:33.126 --> 06:34.360
[horn honks]

06:34.427 --> 06:35.661
- Move it, lady!

06:35.728 --> 06:40.733
- Oh, am I going too slow
for you?

06:40.800 --> 06:42.969
[beeping]

06:43.035 --> 06:45.705
- Guys, we're literally
losing him!

06:45.772 --> 06:48.541
- Don't worry.
He won't give us the slip.

06:50.843 --> 06:53.246
- ♪ Ooh girl
do-do-do ♪

06:53.312 --> 06:54.347
Whoa!

06:54.413 --> 06:56.349
Whoa-oh-oh!

06:57.917 --> 07:01.154
- We still have five minutes
to get it to the post office.

07:01.220 --> 07:04.056
- Let's roll.
- And rock!

07:04.123 --> 07:05.491
[rock music]

07:05.558 --> 07:09.028
[thump]
Dudes, I can't play action music

07:09.095 --> 07:11.898
if there's no action.

07:11.964 --> 07:13.466
- Bad news, guys.

07:13.533 --> 07:16.169
We pushed Vanzilla too hard.

07:16.235 --> 07:18.638
[together] No!

07:18.704 --> 07:21.407
{\an3}- Hey, guys,
check out the new look!

07:21.474 --> 07:24.610
{\an1}- Leni, this isn't the time
to talk about fashion.

07:26.312 --> 07:28.581
<i>♪</i> ♪

07:28.648 --> 07:31.784
- I never thought I'd say this,
but good thinking, Leni.

07:31.851 --> 07:34.587
{\an1}- I got the idea from Lincoln's
coloring book.

07:36.789 --> 07:39.492
- Thanks for the tow!
[pig oinks]

07:39.559 --> 07:41.861
- Just hurry up
and make us famous!

07:44.096 --> 07:48.234
[together] This needs
to be mailed by four o'clock.

07:48.301 --> 07:50.136
What are you doing here?

07:50.203 --> 07:51.938
- Is that a comic book?

07:52.004 --> 07:53.472
- A what? No.

07:53.539 --> 07:56.542
{\an3}I mean, shouldn't you boys be
in detention?

07:58.678 --> 08:00.146
- It is a comic book.

08:00.213 --> 08:03.182
{\an1}"The Adventures of Ace Savvy
and the Principal Valiant"

08:03.249 --> 08:04.984
by Wilbur T. Huggins.

08:05.051 --> 08:08.321
- [gasps] You're entering
the Ace Savvy contest?

08:08.387 --> 08:10.289
- And your name is Wilbur?

08:10.356 --> 08:12.491
{\an3}- Look!
New commemorative stamps!

08:14.894 --> 08:16.128
{\an3}Aah! Oof!

08:16.195 --> 08:18.464
{\an1}- So that's why you confiscated
our comic book

08:18.531 --> 08:20.066
and put us in detention:

08:20.132 --> 08:21.400
to knock us out of the running!

08:21.467 --> 08:23.936
- Okay, okay, I did it,
but I had to.

08:24.003 --> 08:25.771
When I heard
how great your comic was,

08:25.838 --> 08:27.773
I knew mine wouldn't
stand a chance.

08:27.840 --> 08:30.676
{\an1}- But, sir, why is a comic book
contest so important to you?

08:30.743 --> 08:32.678
{\an1}You're a successful
school administrator.

08:32.745 --> 08:34.013
You've got your own golf cart.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.815
- Yes, it's true.
I have it all.

08:35.881 --> 08:37.917
But it wasn't always this way.

08:37.984 --> 08:41.053
<i>When I was your age,</i>
<i>I didn't have a lot of friends.</i>

08:41.120 --> 08:42.520
<i>But I had Ace.</i>

08:42.587 --> 08:43.623
Yeah! Get 'em, Ace!

08:43.688 --> 08:45.324
Way to deal out some justice!

08:45.391 --> 08:47.860
[baseball bat thwacks]

08:47.927 --> 08:49.962
[all laughing]

08:50.029 --> 08:51.163
- Look at him!

08:51.230 --> 08:53.032
- Those comics meant the world
to me.

08:53.099 --> 08:55.635
{\an3}I wanted to win the contest
so I could meet Bill Buck

08:55.701 --> 08:58.471
and thank him for getting me
through a lonely childhood.

08:58.537 --> 09:01.173
{\an3}But I went too far.
I'm sorry, boys.

09:01.240 --> 09:03.042
You deserve to win. Not me.

09:03.109 --> 09:08.147
As Ace Savvy would say,
deal me out.

09:08.214 --> 09:10.583
{\an1}- Wow. I guess there's more
to Huggins than meets the eye.

09:10.650 --> 09:14.553
- Yeah. And his story
just gave me an idea.

09:14.620 --> 09:16.188
both: Principal Huggins, wait!

09:16.255 --> 09:19.292
{\an1}- Oh, yes, of course.
You'll need my administrator ID

09:19.358 --> 09:21.027
{\an1}to report me
to the school board.

09:21.093 --> 09:22.962
- No!
We're not reporting anyone.

09:23.029 --> 09:24.363
Clyde and I get it.

09:24.430 --> 09:26.332
Ace has gotten us
through some tough times too.

09:26.399 --> 09:28.901
{\an3}- Yeah, like when Lori
first got together with Bobby.

09:28.968 --> 09:32.305
{\an3}It was a rainy Tuesday.
I wore suede shoes.

09:32.371 --> 09:33.439
That was a mistake.

09:33.506 --> 09:35.274
{\an1}- I think he gets the idea,
Clyde.

09:35.341 --> 09:37.543
And we're not mad,
because you just gave us

09:37.610 --> 09:39.378
a much better ending
for our comic.

09:39.445 --> 09:40.880
- I did?
- You did.

09:40.947 --> 09:42.748
{\an3}But we got to hurry.
We only have a minute.

09:42.815 --> 09:45.184
{\an1}- I think I can buy you
a few minutes.

09:45.251 --> 09:46.652
<i>[jazz music]</i>

09:46.719 --> 09:48.955
{\an1}- I'm sorry, sir.
We're closing.

09:49.021 --> 09:50.189
Ooh.

09:50.256 --> 09:52.625
- Hello, Mrs... Lee, is it?

09:52.692 --> 09:55.061
{\an3}I believe your son Wyatt
attends my school.

09:55.127 --> 09:58.464
{\an3}How would he like
a little extra recess?

09:58.531 --> 10:01.067
Maybe a get-out-of-gym pass?

10:04.303 --> 10:08.074
{\an3}- Willy, why do you always have
to play dirty cards?

10:08.140 --> 10:11.444
- I'm not an evil guy.
I was just dealt a bad hand.

10:11.510 --> 10:15.448
As a lonely kid, the only game
I knew was solitaire.

10:15.514 --> 10:17.817
So I guess it's off to jail
for me.

10:17.883 --> 10:20.252
- I have a better idea.

10:20.319 --> 10:21.754
[tires screech]

10:21.821 --> 10:23.856
- The Old Maid's making off
with the jackpot!

10:23.923 --> 10:28.761
- You'll never catch me, Savvy!
[laughs]

10:28.828 --> 10:30.663
- Oh, I wouldn't be so sure,

10:30.730 --> 10:33.632
{\an3}'cause we've got a new card
to play.

10:33.699 --> 10:36.569
- Time to deal out some justice.

10:39.438 --> 10:41.640
- I love the ending!

10:41.707 --> 10:45.311
Especially when we learn
Wild Card was a lonely kid.

10:45.378 --> 10:48.647
I read a lot of entries
with great action sequences,

10:48.714 --> 10:51.450
but none with this kind
of heart.

10:51.517 --> 10:53.552
{\an1}- It was inspired
by our principal here.

10:53.619 --> 10:55.488
He really wanted to meet you.

10:55.554 --> 10:58.691
{\an1}- Sir, it is an honor.
I just never--

10:58.758 --> 11:02.028
{\an1}ah, this is the best day of my--
[sighs]

11:03.396 --> 11:06.499
- Hey, what did you think
of the Queen of Diamonds?

11:06.565 --> 11:08.234
Wasn't she your favorite part?

11:08.300 --> 11:11.137
Here. Let me show you some
of my ideas for an action figure

11:11.203 --> 11:12.171
and a bed sheet set.

11:12.238 --> 11:14.073
[all shouting at once]

11:14.140 --> 11:17.810
{\an3}- Whoa. This is kind of
a full house.

11:22.348 --> 11:25.284
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

11:25.351 --> 11:32.491
<i>♪</i> ♪

11:34.927 --> 11:36.996
[bird tweeting]

11:37.063 --> 11:38.397
[cat meows]

11:38.464 --> 11:40.900
- Hey, guys, we're home!

11:43.836 --> 11:46.372
- How's my Felis catus?
- Oh, you're so cute!

11:46.439 --> 11:48.874
I love you so much!
- Yes, you are!

11:48.941 --> 11:50.810
- Sit, Charles.

11:50.876 --> 11:53.379
Now shake.

11:53.446 --> 11:55.614
Now play dead.

11:55.681 --> 11:58.551
{\an3}- Dearly beloved,
we are gathered here today...

11:58.617 --> 12:00.086
- Get the dot! Go get the dot!

12:00.152 --> 12:02.888
- I'm trying,
but it's going too fast!

12:02.955 --> 12:05.057
[baby laughing]

12:05.124 --> 12:07.827
- Guys! Guess what I found!

12:07.893 --> 12:09.428
[dog whimpers]

12:09.495 --> 12:11.730
- Ooh! Pretty earmuffs. Give me!

12:11.797 --> 12:15.134
- They're not earmuffs.
This is a dog.

12:15.201 --> 12:16.569
I found it wandering
in the park.

12:16.635 --> 12:18.137
It doesn't have a collar.

12:18.204 --> 12:19.472
all: Aww!

12:19.538 --> 12:22.341
[all speaking at once]

12:22.408 --> 12:24.743
- Are you hungry, little guy?

12:24.810 --> 12:26.679
{\an1}- Dudes, we should give him
a treat.

12:26.745 --> 12:28.380
- I was literally just going
to say that.

12:28.447 --> 12:30.749
Except for the "dudes" part.

12:30.816 --> 12:31.917
[dog barks]

12:34.353 --> 12:35.554
[dog barks, cat meows]

12:35.621 --> 12:37.456
[bird tweets, hamster squeaks]

12:38.958 --> 12:40.192
- Aw, sorry, guys.

12:40.259 --> 12:41.427
You can have treats anytime.

12:41.494 --> 12:44.163
{\an1}Right now this poor lost doggie
is hungry.

12:44.230 --> 12:45.731
[all groan]

12:46.932 --> 12:49.768
- Aww!
- Lay your weary head

12:49.835 --> 12:50.903
to rest, brah.

12:50.970 --> 12:53.672
- Uh, that's his butt.
- Bogus.

12:53.739 --> 12:56.809
[cat meows]
- Ow, Cliff! No claws.

12:58.811 --> 13:01.447
{\an1}- Ahh. I loaned the puppy
my toothbrush,

13:01.514 --> 13:03.949
so now we're both ready for bed.

13:04.016 --> 13:06.018
{\an3}- Well, too bad he's sleeping
with me.

13:06.085 --> 13:08.154
{\an3}- I don't want to get <i> ruff</i>
with you,

13:08.220 --> 13:09.755
but he's sleeping with me.

13:09.822 --> 13:10.856
- Nuh-uh!

13:10.923 --> 13:12.791
He's sleeping in my bed!
- False!

13:12.858 --> 13:14.093
[whistle blows]

13:14.160 --> 13:16.929
- Fear not, siblings.
I have the solution.

13:16.996 --> 13:19.265
{\an3}There are eight hours of sleep
and eleven siblings

13:19.331 --> 13:20.499
{\an3}who desire to share
their slumber

13:20.566 --> 13:22.034
with the adorable canine.

13:22.101 --> 13:27.439
{\an1}Therefore, said canine will
spend 43.6 minutes in each bed.

13:27.506 --> 13:29.441
all: Agreed!

13:31.877 --> 13:34.046
{\an3}- Sorry, buddy.
I got to keep this spot free

13:34.113 --> 13:36.482
for my 43.6 minutes.

13:36.549 --> 13:37.750
[dog whimpers]
- Sorry, Walt.

13:37.816 --> 13:40.452
- Sorry, Cliff.
- Sorry, Geo.

13:40.519 --> 13:42.087
[dog groans]

13:42.154 --> 13:45.090
[meowing, squeaking, chirping]

13:46.959 --> 13:49.795
- [barking]
<i>- Pets for sale!</i>

13:49.862 --> 13:53.299
<i>Come get your pre-owned,</i>
<i>previously loved pets!</i>

13:53.365 --> 13:55.067
[cat yowling]

14:00.005 --> 14:01.907
[cat yowls]

14:01.974 --> 14:03.809
[animals cheer]

14:03.876 --> 14:05.444
[whispering]

14:09.281 --> 14:10.482
- [whistles]

14:10.549 --> 14:12.718
- [barking]

14:17.389 --> 14:18.724
[glass shatters]

14:19.959 --> 14:23.162
{\an1}- [gasps] Our wedding present
from Aunt Ruth!

14:23.229 --> 14:27.032
I have been wanting to get rid
of that ugly thing for years,

14:27.099 --> 14:28.400
but I felt too guilty.

14:28.467 --> 14:30.369
You get a treat.

14:30.436 --> 14:32.137
Oops, that's your butt.

14:33.906 --> 14:36.842
{\an3}- [humming]

14:41.113 --> 14:43.182
You ate the whole thing? Oh!

14:43.249 --> 14:44.950
Finally someone who appreciates

14:45.017 --> 14:47.620
my liverwurst, shrimp,
and hot mayo casserole!

14:47.686 --> 14:50.222
{\an3}[sighs] Usually,
eating it's a one way ticket

14:50.289 --> 14:52.024
to the sink or toilet, huh?

14:52.091 --> 14:53.892
[stomachs growl]

15:08.674 --> 15:10.743
- [gasps, then giggles]

15:14.113 --> 15:15.214
- [barks]

15:19.551 --> 15:20.953
{\an3}[barks]

15:24.089 --> 15:26.158
{\an1}[barks]

15:26.225 --> 15:29.161
[all speaking at once]

15:30.362 --> 15:33.299
<i>foreboding music]</i>

15:33.365 --> 15:34.566
<i>♪</i> ♪

15:34.633 --> 15:39.204
{\an3}- [gasps]
Look at those muddy paws!

15:39.271 --> 15:41.440
- You know what that means!

15:41.507 --> 15:42.608
all: Bath time!

15:42.675 --> 15:44.510
- I'll grab my loofah!
- Yeah!

15:44.576 --> 15:46.312
- Look at this little puppy!

15:46.378 --> 15:48.113
{\an3}- [barks]

15:57.990 --> 16:00.225
<i>- Green Mile Pet Sanctuary.</i>
<i>This is Schmitty.</i>

16:00.292 --> 16:01.427
<i>How may I help you?</i>

16:01.493 --> 16:03.162
- [barking]

16:03.228 --> 16:05.130
<i>- You sound like a stray,</i>
<i>little doggie.</i>

16:05.197 --> 16:07.533
<i>Keep on barking</i>
<i>so I can track your location.</i>

16:07.599 --> 16:09.902
{\an1}- [barks]

16:09.968 --> 16:11.637
<i>- Got you!</i>

16:13.639 --> 16:15.207
{\an3}- [barking]

16:15.274 --> 16:16.909
- [whistles]

16:24.550 --> 16:25.918
- [whines]

16:32.958 --> 16:36.462
- Schmitty, this is Corinne.
Got your stray. Over.

16:36.528 --> 16:38.230
[engine revs]

16:39.565 --> 16:41.800
<i>[peaceful music]</i>

16:47.706 --> 16:50.309
<i>- We'll return</i>
<i>to the 12:30 movie after this.</i>

16:50.376 --> 16:54.113
<i>- Here at the</i>
<i>Green Mile Pet Sanctuary,</i>

16:54.179 --> 16:56.348
<i>we need your help.</i>

16:56.415 --> 17:00.819
<i>All of these cute little</i>
<i>animals need a home.</i>

17:00.886 --> 17:03.389
<i>For just the cost</i>
<i>of a cup of coffee,</i>

17:03.455 --> 17:07.760
<i>you could save the life of an</i>
<i>adorable, helpless friend.</i>

17:07.826 --> 17:10.729
<i>Won't you adopt one today?</i>

17:10.796 --> 17:13.598
<i>Green Mile Pet Sanctuary.</i>

17:15.800 --> 17:18.936
- [barking]

17:22.775 --> 17:25.911
<i>[adventure music]</i>

17:25.978 --> 17:32.918
<i>♪</i> ♪

17:35.654 --> 17:37.656
- [meows]

17:37.723 --> 17:39.258
- [meowing]

17:43.695 --> 17:50.836
<i>♪</i> ♪

17:57.342 --> 17:58.477
[phone rings]

17:58.544 --> 17:59.778
- Green Mile Pet Sanctuary.

17:59.845 --> 18:01.947
This is Schmitty.
How can I help you?

18:10.589 --> 18:12.191
What the heck?

18:23.335 --> 18:24.803
all: Shh!

18:29.441 --> 18:31.276
- [whimpers]

18:31.343 --> 18:33.011
[barks]

18:34.346 --> 18:36.114
[barks]
all: Shh!

18:40.652 --> 18:42.321
- Cheap, crummy monitors.

18:42.387 --> 18:45.591
Mmm, like those lumps.

18:45.657 --> 18:47.659
Hey! Get back here!

18:50.295 --> 18:51.597
Doh!

18:51.663 --> 18:56.802
<i>♪</i> ♪

18:57.970 --> 19:01.607
- Oh, yeah! Corinne for the win!

19:01.673 --> 19:03.809
<i>Schmitty, this is Corinne.</i>
<i>Over.</i>

19:03.876 --> 19:06.111
I apprehended the fugitive
and his accomplices.

19:06.178 --> 19:08.180
We're gonna need
four more cages. Over.

19:08.247 --> 19:11.250
[maniacal laughter]
Over.

19:13.452 --> 19:16.388
[growling and screeching]

19:18.824 --> 19:21.760
<i>[heroic music]</i>

19:21.827 --> 19:28.734
<i>♪</i> ♪

19:29.701 --> 19:31.637
- What? Oh, no, you don't.

19:31.703 --> 19:33.739
[tires squeal]

19:33.805 --> 19:36.542
[laughter]

19:36.608 --> 19:38.777
Whoa!

19:40.913 --> 19:42.381
- [barks]

19:43.849 --> 19:45.150
- [laughs]

19:45.217 --> 19:47.753
Nice try, you little
troublemakers.

19:47.819 --> 19:49.221
[thud]

19:49.288 --> 19:51.523
[laughs] Got you!

19:51.590 --> 19:54.793
You got to get up pretty early
in the mor--

19:54.860 --> 19:56.295
- [barking]

19:56.361 --> 19:59.331
- Well, yeah, that one,
but he'll get his.

19:59.398 --> 20:02.134
<i>[dark music]</i>

20:02.200 --> 20:05.370
Oh, but don't you worry.
I'll find that--

20:05.437 --> 20:07.339
- [snarling]
- Huh?

20:07.406 --> 20:10.509
<i>[heroic music]</i>

20:10.576 --> 20:12.244
{\an3}Ow!

20:12.311 --> 20:13.779
{\an3}[screaming]

20:19.217 --> 20:22.721
- Well, Clyde hasn't seen them.
- Neither has Bobby.

20:22.788 --> 20:24.656
{\an3}Come on. We have to go look
for them.

20:24.723 --> 20:26.792
Everyone, bring your posters.

20:26.858 --> 20:30.562
- I don't know what I'm gonna do
if we don't find them! [crying]

20:30.629 --> 20:33.799
{\an1}- Whilst I normally view animals
as mere test subjects,

20:33.865 --> 20:37.536
those little guys are family.

20:37.603 --> 20:39.605
[all crying]

20:39.671 --> 20:40.839
{\an3}[dog barks]

20:40.906 --> 20:43.108
{\an3}- Sometimes I can still
hear them.

20:43.175 --> 20:45.444
[all crying]
[dog barking]

20:45.510 --> 20:47.446
Wait!

20:47.512 --> 20:50.449
[all cheering]

20:50.515 --> 20:51.783
- [whining]

20:51.850 --> 20:53.819
[all speaking at once]

20:53.885 --> 20:56.555
- You, too, new puppy!
Get in here.

20:56.622 --> 20:58.890
You're part of our family, too.

20:58.957 --> 21:00.525
[together]
You're an official Loud.

21:00.592 --> 21:02.561
[doorbell rings]

21:02.628 --> 21:05.497
- Hi. My name's Clare.
I'm looking for my dog.

21:05.564 --> 21:09.868
{\an3}He slipped out of his collar,
and--Watterson!

21:09.935 --> 21:12.838
{\an3}There you are!
I've missed you!

21:12.904 --> 21:14.606
Oh! How I've missed you!

21:14.673 --> 21:17.843
{\an3}He's my best friend
in the whole wide world.

21:17.909 --> 21:20.012
Thank you for taking care
of him.

21:20.078 --> 21:22.147
- It was literally our pleasure.

21:22.214 --> 21:25.984
- Aw, looks like you're
going home, little dude.

21:26.051 --> 21:29.054
- Uh, Luna, that's his butt.

21:29.121 --> 21:31.923
{\an1}- Bye, Watterson.
I'm sorry you won't be a Loud,

21:31.990 --> 21:34.459
{\an1}but I'm glad
your friend found you.

21:34.526 --> 21:36.995
{\an3}- [barks]
- Come on, Watterson.

21:37.062 --> 21:39.297
Time to get you home.

21:39.364 --> 21:40.465
all: Bye!

21:40.532 --> 21:42.834
- We'll miss you!
- Love you!

21:46.371 --> 21:49.941
{\an3}- Come on, Watterson!
Come on, boy!

21:52.444 --> 21:54.179
- We're so glad you're home.

21:54.246 --> 21:57.582
{\an3}How about we all go to the
kitchen for a nice big treat?

22:00.085 --> 22:02.521
{\an1}- Does anyone know
why my slide projector was

22:02.587 --> 22:04.623
in Charles' dog house?

22:10.529 --> 22:11.963
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:12.030 --> 22:13.799
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:13.865 --> 22:16.768
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.835 --> 22:19.237
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.304 --> 22:23.308
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.375 --> 22:24.676
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.743 --> 22:26.078
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.144 --> 22:27.446
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.512 --> 22:28.680
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.747 --> 22:30.115
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.182 --> 22:32.651
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.718 --> 22:35.187
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.253 --> 22:36.555
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
